<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Reports Leading Exports Drop </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2203185294 </F>
<F P=103> PA2203185294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] According to the Ecuadoran Central Bank, 
the country's leading exports registered a 3.4-percent drop at 
the end of 1993. Revenues from the sale of oil, bananas, 
shrimp, cacao, and seafood amounted to $2.9 billion compared to 
$3 billion earned in 1992. Oil exports yielded $1.149 billion; 
bananas, $503 million; and shrimp, $451 million. (Quito Voz de 
los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 15 Mar 94) 

</TEXT>

