<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2403233494 </F>
<F P=103> PY2403233494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Uruguay monitored through 24 
March. 
  The Central Bank's money supply dropped 3.7 percent in 
January and increased 4.4 percent in February. The monetary base 
decreased $164.4 million. (Montevideo BUSQUEDA in Spanish 10 Mar 
94 p 24) 
  The National Statistics Institute reported that in January 
the unemployment rate was 8 percent of the economically active 
population, the lowest rate in the past few years. The 
employment rate was 58.1 percent. (Montevideo BUSQUEDA in 
Spanish 10 Mar 94 p 26) 

