<F P=102>  PA2403192294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1609 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Elizabeth Diaz Otero from Los Pinos Presidential </F>
Residence; from the "Panorama Newscast" -- live] 
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari returned a few 
minutes ago to the Los Pinos official residence. He was at the 
Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI] national headquarters, 
where he stood in an honor guard before Luis Donaldo Colosio's 
coffin. As we all know, he accompanied the body from the Mexico 
City international airport to the party's headquarters. The 
president was accompanied by his wife, Cecilia Ocheli de 
Salinas, and he was obviously dismayed. He told us he has lost 
his great friend and asked us to respect his sorrow. Let us 
listen to the recording. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] I have just stood in an honor 
guard 
before the body of Luis Donaldo Colosio. I went to the airport 
to pick up his widow, Diana Laura, and to pick him up. My wife 
and I accompanied her. Just a few minutes ago, we also 
accompanied her to her vehicle when she decided to leave. 
  I want to tell you that Mexico has lost a great man, and I 
have lost a great friend. I want to ask you to allow us to 
mourn him, and bid him farewell. Thank you. [end recording] 
  President Salinas' agenda today is private. Nonetheless, it 
is expected that at noon he will receive [Canadian] Prime 
Minister Jean Chretien, with whom he had to interrupt his 
discussions yesterday when the attack occurred which took the 
life of Luis Donaldo Colosio. 

</TEXT>

