<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Minister Advocates Strengthening Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2603014694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2034 GMT 
25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2603014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hungarian Foreign Minister Geza Jeszenszky has 
stated that he believes that ties between Hungary and Cuba 
should be strengthened in all spheres. Jeszenszky meet with 
Cuban Ambassador to Hungary (Carlos Grego Soso) [name and title 
as heard] in Budapest. Jeszenszky said that despite the reasons 
that initially obstructed Hungarian-Cuban relations, during the 
current period of change the development of bilateral ties 
should be promoted, taking advantage of mutually beneficial 
elements. 
  In another meeting, (Janos Marcandi), deputy secretary of 
state at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, also expressed his 
interest in reviving relations with Cuba, specifically in the 
financial arena. (Marcandi) expressed his hope that formulas can 
be found through which financial collaboration will be possible 
under the new conditions, even though the distance makes trade 
more difficult. 

