<H3> <TI>   Division General Emphasizes Combat Readiness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2603032894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2603032894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During a 25 March meeting with young pilots held at 
the Antiaircraft Defense and Revolutionary Air Force [DAAFAR] 
Museum in Havana, Division General Enrique Carreras highlighted 
the high level of combat readiness of the new generations of 
pilots. 
  [Begin Carreras recording] At the Bay of Pigs, that small 
air 
force made a significant contribution to victory. I believe that 
the DAAFAR in Angola proved that those young people have 
demonstrated in the field, in reality, during operations and all 
the difficult moments we faced there, the great competency of 
our DAAFAR forces. [end recording] 
  Other issues discussed at the meeting were the efforts made 
by our Air Force during the search for Commander Camilo 
Cienfuegos, as well as Bay of Pigs operations and the 5 
September 1957 events. 
  The meeting was held to commemorate the 50th anniversary of 
the graduation from pilot school of Division General Enrique 
Carreras, Hero of the Republic of Cuba. 

</TEXT>

