<H3> <TI>   ANIR Role in Defense, Sugar, Food Evaluated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2503222494 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2503222494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Havana, a plenum of the national committee of the 
National Association of Innovators and Efficiency Experts [ANIR] 
is evaluating ANIR's role in defense, the sugar harvest, and the 
food program. 
  Politburo member Maria de los Angeles Garcia stressed that, 
in addition to their continuous efforts to find solutions to the 
nation's other problems, ANIR members should look upon 
preserving equipment, machinery, tools, and other resources -- 
many of which are not being used because of the lack of spare 
parts -- as a challenge. As regards ANIR's participation in the 
sugar harvest, the plenum agreed on the need to expedite the 
recyling and production of spare parts needed to operate 
combines, compressors, and boilers at the sugar mills, as well 
as to use animal-powered equipment more efficiently. 

</TEXT>

