<F P=100> Caribbean </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pig Raising Prohibited in Central Havana City </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2503172994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2503172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jorge Rogabruna, vice director of hygiene and 
epidemiology in Havana City Province, said that the law that 
prohibits the rearing of pigs in the central municipalities of 
the capital and in apartment buildings and city neighborhoods 
remains valid. He stated that in Centro Habana, Habana Vieja, 
Cerro, Plaza de la Revolucion, Playa, and Diez de Octubre the 
rearing of those animals is prohibited and that it is not 
authorized in urban localities of other municipalities in Havana 
City with large concentrations of people. Rogabruna said that 
there are control mechanisms at the zone and municipal levels 
through the people's councils which send commissions to visit 
the owners of the animals and warn them of the infraction they 
commit by keeping those animals. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

