Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Revolutionary Front for the Promotion and 
Progress of Haiti, FRAPH, have called on ministers from the 
resigning government to refrain from going to their offices. 
This is their ultimatum. FRAPH is threatening to dislodge the 
ministers of the resigning Malval government. As of 28 March, 
the ministers are no longer to go to their offices. 
  FRAPH has harshly criticized the management of the resigning 
government. During a news conference held by FRAPH leaders on 24 
March, the most virulent criticism was aimed at the ministers of 
health, agriculture, and education. [passage omitted]. 
  [Begin recording] [Emmanuel Constant, in Creole] We are 
asking that all the current ministers of Malval's resigning 
government stop going to work, as the parliament directed. We 
are very serious about this. We are asking all the ministers not 
to go to work on 28 March. 
  [Louis Jodel Chambelin] If they do not obey, the Haitian 
people will come and remove them. And I hope that the next 
government arrests all the directors general and the ministers, 
so they can explain what they did with the Haitian people's 
money [applause] [end recording] 
  Those were FRAPH leaders Emmanuel Constant and Louis Jodel 
Chambelain. 

