<H3> <TI>   Colosio Assassin Tied to `Several' Armed Groups </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603171694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1600 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2603171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Mario Aburto Martinez, who assassinated Luis Donaldo 
Colosio Murrieta, had maintained ties with several armed groups 
in various Mexican states, according to his testimony before the 
attorney general moments after murdering the PRI [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party] candidate. Aburto refused, however, to 
name the armed groups and the regions in which they operate or 
to say whether he acted alone or if the assassination was part 
of a plot. He also denied belonging in the past or at present to 
any political party or religious sect. 

</TEXT>

