<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Created To Investigate Colosio Murder </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2503200394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1500 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2503200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Mexican Congress factions have unanimously 
approved the creation of a special multiparty commission to 
investigate Luis Donaldo Colosio's assassination. 
  The Congress' Permanent Commission signed an agreement 
declaring 25 March a day of national mourning for Colosio's 
death. The agreement was signed by the 10 parliamentary 
factions represented in the legislative body. The multiparty 
commission also agreed unanimously to conduct the investigation 
and keep the Legislative Branch informed. 
  This commission is made up of Senators Ernesto Lucre of PRI 
[Institutional Revolutionary Party] and Hector Teran of PAN 
[National Action Party], as well as Deputies Gustavo Carvajal of 
PRI, Alejandro Alcidas of PRD [Party of the Democratic 
Revolution], Alfredo Castaneda of PARM [Authentic Party of the 
Mexican Revolution], Juan de Dios Castro of PAN, and Cuauthemoc 
Amezcua of PPS [Popular Socialist Party]. 

</TEXT>

