<H3> <TI>   PAN Official on Economy, Assassination Inquiry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603032294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2603032294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Luis Armenta; from the "ACIR Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Today Gonzalo Altamirano Dimas, National Action 
Party [PAN] deputy and president of this political institution 
in the Federal District, said no one should bet on the worsening 
of economic and political problems. He pointed out that even 
though the Mexican Stock Market has seen a decrease in the 
number of transactions, this is a natural phenomenon because of 
the recent assassination of Luis Donaldo Colosio [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party, PRI, presidential candidate]. In an 
interview, Gonzalo Altamirano Dimas said stability in the 
Mexican Stock Market will depend on immediate actions by the 
government. 
  [Begin Altamirano recording] The interests of the country 
should prevail over other interests no matter how legitimate 
they may be. We want the death of Colosio to be cleared up and 
explained. We join the demand that exists. We want an in-depth 
investigation. Those responsible should be arrested and 
punished with the full weight of the law. We also believe the 
1994 election process should be clean and legitimate. I believe 
it all goes together. Whoever wants to bet against this 
situation would be sowing uncertainty and possibly violence in 
the country. We do not want that. [end recording] 
  Gonzalo Altamirano Dimas, president of the PAN in the 
capital, also said the PRI should have a new presidential 
candidate soon because he will have to conduct an intense 
campaign as the opposition is already getting the citizens' 
support. 
  In addition, deputies from the Party of the Democratic 
Revolution [PRD] rejected all kinds of violence and sent their 
condolences to the relatives of Luis Donaldo Colosio. In a news 
conference, the PRD deputies demanded a thorough investigation 
of the PRI candidate's assassination and demanded that those 
found guilty be punished. PRD Deputy Alejandro Encinas said the 
commission that will investigate the attack on Luis Donaldo 
Colosio has begun to operate and will be in Tijuana on Saturday 
to meet with the high-ranking federal authorities. The PRD 
deputy said the area where the attack took place will be studied 
and a detailed report will be drafted that will be submitted on 
Monday to the Congressional Permanent Commission, which will 
also hold sessions on that day. That is all we have for now. 

</TEXT>

