<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Denies Extradition of Colombian Drug Trafficker </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603023194 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2603023194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Supreme Court of Justice, in a plenary session, 
has studied the case of drug trafficker (Jacobo Lerner 
Zimmerman) in detail. Chief Magistrate Arturo Hoyos believes 
that keeping him in jail is the right decision. 
  [Begin Hoyos recording] The habeas corpus we reviewed refers 
to crimes (Mr. Lerner Zimmerman) is accused of committing in the 
Republic of Panama. Regarding said accusations, the Supreme 
Court finds that there is sufficient evidence to hold this 
person in connection with these drug-related crimes against the 
public. [end recording] 
  It is noteworthy that (Jacobo Lerner Zimmerman), a Colombian 
citizen involved in drug trafficking, is wanted by the United 
States for the same crime. The Supreme Court, however, has 
already denied an extradition request. 
  [Begin Hoyos recording] There is a ruling by the Criminal 
Court that denies the extradition request, and that ruling must 
be executed. [end recording] 
  In view of this Supreme Court decision, (Jacobo Lerner 
Zimmerman) will have to spend a long time in jail unless he 
escapes, which is not uncommon in the country's jails among 
people connected with drug trafficking. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

