<H3> <TI>   New Cabinet Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603173194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1623 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2603173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] La Paz, 26 Mar (EFE) -- Following a reshuffling of 
his cabinet, this is the makeup of President Gonzalo Sanchez de 
Lozada's new cabinet: 
  President: Gonzalo Sanchez de Lozada, leader of the 
liberal Nationalist Revolutionary Movement (MNR). 
  Vice President: Victor Hugo Cardenas, leader of the Indian 
Tupak Katari Revolutionary Liberation Movement (MRTK-L). 
  Foreign Affairs and Worship Minister: Antonio Aranibar, 
leader of the Free Bolivia Movement (MBL). 
  Economic Development and Finance Minister: Fernando Alvaro 
Cosio (MNR), replacing independent Fernando Illanes. 
  Human Development Minister: Enrique Ipina Melgar (MNR), 
replacing independent Fernando Romero. 
  Sustainable Development Minister: Jose Guillermo 
Justiniano (independent). 
  Government Minister: German Quiroga (MNR). 
  National Defense Minister: Raul Tovar of the Civic 
Solidarity Unity (UCS), replacing Antonio Cespedes (UCS). 
  Social Communication Minister: Ernesto Machicado (MNR), 
replacing Hermann Antelo (MNR). 
  Justice Minister: Rene Blattmann (independent), replacing 
Carlos Morales. 
  Labor Minister: Reynaldo Peters (MNR). 
  Presidency Minister: Carlos Sanchez Berzain (MNR). 
  Minister Without Portfolio: Alfonso Revollo (MNR). 

</TEXT>

