<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lima Municipality Lacks Funds for Salaries, Services </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2503171794 Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 17 Mar 94 p A14 </F>
<F P=103> PY2503171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EXPRESO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ivan Dibos, deputy mayor of the municipality of 
Lima, on 16 March warned of the lack of economic resources 
needed to pay the salaries of the municipality's employees and 
for public sanitation services in Cercado District. 
  He added that this problem must be resolved by the central 
government, taking into account that it affects the public and 
that the problem was created by the government when it 
implemented Legislative Decree No. 776, which pruned the 
municipality's tax benefits. 
  Dibos indicated that this month (March) it will be very 
difficult to cover the employees' payroll, which amounts to some 
4.5 million new soles. 
  He stated that the estimated deficit amounts to 60 million 
new soles per annum. "The problem is very serious, and we do 
not have the resources needed to pay employees' salaries," he 
said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

