<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Confirms Release of Coup Attempt Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603145194 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1329 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2603145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 26 Mar (DPA) -- President Rafael Caldera 
made official on Saturday, 26 March, the release of the main 
leader of the 4 February 1992 coup attempt, Lieutenant Colonel 
Hugo Chavez, who during the early morning hours of today also 
requested his discharge from active duty, Radio Caracas Radio 
(RCR) confirmed today. 
  Chavez, regarded as the ideologue of a movement of midlevel 
officers who in 1992 executed two attempts to overthrow then 
President Carlos Andres Perez, was released after two years in 
jail when the president dropped the charges on the condition the 
officers more deeply involved in the coup attempts do not return 
to the Armed Forces. 
  According to RCR, the lieutenant colonel and other officers 
will create a new political organization that will be based on 
the military movement of the nationalist inspiration Chavez 
created within the Armed Forces and which received the public's 
support. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

