<H3> <TI>   President Caldera Pardons 10 More Officers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2703020894 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 0009 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2703020894 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Along with pardoning Lieutenant Colonel Hugo Chavez 
Frias, President Rafael Caldera has dismissed charges against 10 
other officers involved in the 4 February and 27 November 1992 
coup attempts, all of whom were being held at the San Carlos 
garrison. 
  At 1130 today, Saturday, the 10 officers who received the 
presidential pardon left the old military garrison. They are: 
Captains Antonio Rojas Suarez, Noel Martinez, Edgar Hernandez 
Berens, Guillermo Blanco Acosta, Alcala Cardones, and Aguilar 
Gomez who participated in the 4 February coup attempt. Also 
released were Air Force Lieutenants Jose Baltazar Nelo and Jessy 
Chacon Escanilla, Captain Jose Valera Rumbos, and Army Mayor 
Carlos Lugo Lopez, who had taken part in the 27 November coup 
attempt. 

