<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Secretariat of Defense Denies Bombing Chiapas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2603165394 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1605 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2603165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In its Press Bulletin No. 33, the Secretariat of 
National Defense [SDN] has denied the assertions made in a 
communique datelined 24 March which the rebel group leadership 
in Chiapas State has been circulating. The communique states 
government airplanes released strange gases and bombed areas 
near the Comitan-Altamirano highway, causing serious fires, at 
dawn on 19 March 1994. The SDN hereby informs the public of the 
following: 
  1. The Secretariat of Defense flatly denies airplanes have 
bombed the area of conflict, because Army and Air Force troops 
have not fired a single shot since 12 January, when the 
president of the Republic ordered a unilateral cease-fire. 
  2. The SDN hereby confirms the pledge made in Press 
Bulletin No. 32 issued on 23 March to the effect troop movement 
in the area of conflict has been strictly administrative. 
  3. The SDN once again offers assurances it will not 
execute actions that may hinder the government's resolve to find 
a peaceful solution to the conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

