<H3> <TI>   Supreme Court Chairman Views Wage Increase Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2103155494 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
20 Mar 94 p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2103155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia -- Having heard the statement of President 
Itamar Franco, Federal Supreme Court [STF] Chairman Luiz Octavio 
Gallotti said he will not argue with him. Gallotti insisted 
that the STF decision to convert wages into URV's on the 20th of 
each month has a constitutional foundation and is strictly under 
the jurisdiction of the STF. 
  "Through the unanimous decision of its members, the STF made 
an administrative decision based on the Constitution. This 
subject exclusively concerns the STF. The STF chairman does not 
want contention with representatives of other government 
branches that are just as independent and who ought to seek 
harmony and not confrontation, seeking respect for the 
constitutional rule of independency and harmony among the 
branches. To obey the Constitution is the best way to preserve 
the credibility of the institutions," Gallotti said. 
  Senate President Humberto Lucena (PMDB-PB) [Brazilian 
Democratic Movement Party -- Paraiba] and Chamber of Deputies 
President Inocencio de Oliveira (PFL-PE) [Liberal Front Party -- 
Pernambuco] could not be found yesterday. Lucena yesterday 
accompanied Paraiba Governor Ronaldo Cunha Lima to dedicate 
several public works in different municipalities in Campina 
Grande region. Inocencio spent the day on his farms in 
Pernambuco and Maranhao, transferring cattle from Serra Talhada, 
Pernambuco, to the interior of Maranhao. 

</TEXT>

