<H3> <TI>   Rio University Signs Agreement With Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2203035494 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
18 Mar 94 p 8--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2203035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cuban Government and Rio de Janeiro State 
University (UERJ) have signed an agreement to develop joint 
technological projects in the areas of bioceramics, industrial 
automation, oil technology, and informatics. The result of the 
programs will then be commercialized and the profits divided 
among the participants. 
  The initiative to sign the agreement came from the 
Brazilians. The negotiations began last February with the visit 
of UERJ Rector Hesio Cordeiro and Paulo Jorge Paes Leme, 
director of the Polytechnic Institute, to Havana. 
  Cuban Minister of Higher Education Fernando Vecino Alegret 
was in Rio de Janeiro yesterday to coordinate with Hesio 
Cordeiro the details for signing the agreement. Cordeiro will 
return to Cuba on 20 March to sign the final terms of the 
agreement. 

</TEXT>

