<H3> <TI>   Lage Pays Visit to Spain, Meets Gonzalez </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2403161994 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1930 GMT 23 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2403161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, 23 Mar (PL) -- Carlos Lage, vice president 
of the Cuban Council of State and executive secretary of the 
Cuban Council of Ministers, is currently in Spain on a working 
visit. He has already met with Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez. 
  Cuban diplomatic sources have disclosed that Lage's agenda 
includes meetings with other officials of the Spanish executive 
branch. 
  Lage will meet with Foreign Affairs Minister Javier Solana, 
Economics and Finance Minister Pedro Solbes, and Commerce and 
Tourism Minister Javier Gomez-Navarro. 
  The same sources indicated that Lage will be in Spain until 
25 March, and his visit will focus on the traditional meetings 
and cooperation between the two governments. 
  Jose Luis Rodriguez, minister chairman of the state 
committee 
for finance, adviser Ernesto Senti, and Cuban Ambassador to 
Spain Rosario Navas are attending the meetings with Lage. 

</TEXT>

