<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bishops Leader: Franco Right on Salary Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2603014794 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2603014794 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today in Rio de Janeiro, Bishop Luciano Mendes, 
president of the National Conference of Brazilian Bishops, said 
that President Itamar Franco is handling the crisis with the 
judicial branch correctly. According to Mendes, the president 
has been showing goodwill and he is seeking to reach an 
agreement that does not harm the Brazilian people: 
  [Begin Mendes recording] Our expectation is that in such a 
moment [words indistinct] generalized and reach a situation in 
which the Federal Supreme Court, STF, would accept indications 
about the collective agreement renewal date for payment of 
salaries to its personnel; would give up interpreting the 
provisional measure text as if it called for moving up the date 
to convert salaries into the Real Value Unit, URV; and the 
president would see his proposal accepted, as he expected. It is 
expected of the president, however, that he recognizes the STF's 
autonomy and authority. [end recording] 
  Despite disagreements between these government branches, 
Mendes believes the two institutions will be strengthened by the 
crisis and that democracy in our country will become more 
consolidated. 

</TEXT>

