<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-059 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Genebaldo Correia Resigns To Avoid Losing Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2303001794 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 
22 Mar 94 p A9 </F>

<F P=103> PY2303001794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brasilia -- Deputy Genebaldo Correia (PMDB-BA 
[Brazilian Democratic Movement Party-Bahia State]), who the 
Budget CPA [Congressional Investigating Committee] has charged 
with corruption, resigned his congressional mandate on 21 March 
to avoid being dismissed, and thereby, losing his political 
rights for three years. 
  Correia's resignation nullifies a procedure, involving 17 
congressmen incriminated by the CPI, to strip him of his 
congressional mandate. The Chamber of Deputies Constitution and 
Justice Committee (CCJ) has handled the procedure. Genebaldo 
delivered a speech, marked by emotion, in a quiet voice. He was 
unable to prevent shedding a few tears. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

