<H3> <TI>   First Air Raid Drill Staged in Pinar del Rio </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2803023694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2803023694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Western Army territory is the first military 
community protected from a possible air attack. Today was an 
unusual Sunday for the inhabitants of the Silvio Caro community 
in Bahia Honda Municipality. At mid-morning, an air raid drill 
broke the people's routine and daily chores. Without panic, well 
disciplined, and well organized, each citizen occupied his or 
her place in the people's tunnels. Students and the children 
from a childcare center also demonstrated their preparation and 
knowledge, finding safe shelter in a few minutes. 
  Silvio Caro, with 2,000 inhabitants, is the first military 
community declared protected against a possible enemy air raid. 
In an act of revolutionary reaffirmation, the Western Army 
community staged an emulation action. Division General Nestor 
Lopez Cuba [rank as heard], head of the Political Board of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces, congratulated the inhabitants of 
Silvio Caro and asked them to keep up their efforts toward 
readiness preparation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

