<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alarcon Attends End of Villa Clara Parliaments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2703210994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2703210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Villa Clara, Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, 
president of the National Assembly of the People's Government 
and Politburo member, has said that one of the clearest 
conclusions of the Parliaments in the Workplaces is that workers 
want to save socialism. Alarcon participated in the conclusion 
of the parliament assemblies in Villa Clara, which concludes 
this process at the provincial level. 
  Speaking to deputies and union leaders in Villa Clara, 
Alarcon de Quesada said that Villa Clara workers agree on the 
need to preserve the achievements of the Revolution and reject 
the IMF formula. Let no one think that capitalist formulas will 
solve the problems of the great majority of the population, he 
said. Alarcon de Quesada went on to say that after four years of 
the special period, there are signs of economic recovery. 

</TEXT>

