<H3> <TI>   TRABAJADORES Evaluates Parliament in Workplace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2803174694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1255 
GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2803174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An editorial carried today in the weekly 
TRABAJADORES says the Parliament in the Workplace assemblies 
have not only strengthened the unions but also buttressed the 
administration, and political and ideological work has also been 
reinforced. The line our population is defending is that of 
finding solutions within socialism, within the social justice 
and equality that the work of the Revolution guarantees. 
  Administrations at the level of centers, enterprises, 
branches, and ministries made a noteworthy contribution to the 
parliament in the workplace assemblies. In a majority of cases, 
they provided serious information and elements that contributed 
to the quality of the analyses made. 
  For its part, the workers movement is obliged to think about 
how to get this method, this work style, to take permanent root 
within its union organizations. The main thing is that 
ideological influence, organizational work, or a thrust toward 
defense or cultural development cannot even be conceived if the 
unions do not participate in solving the economy's real problems. 
  There is no room for pessimism. What we are doing, including 
these Parliament in the Workplace assemblies, is our own victory 
alternative. An editorial carried in today's, 28 March, edition 
of the weekly TRABAJADORES says the initial step has been taken. 

</TEXT>

