<H3> <TI>   Telephone Lines, Services for Granma Populace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2803212494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2010 GMT 
28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2803212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More than 509 km of telephone lines have already 
been installed in the mountainous areas of Granma Province, 
where 17 percent of Granma's population is congregated. An 
important element of the province's mountainous areas is that in 
1993, approximately 1,700 people moved to areas of the Sierra 
Maestra; so far this year, 300 more people have moved into the 
area. 
  As part of the development of the Turquino plan, the whole 
province is covered by the family doctor plan and education and 
health centers for the population have already been guaranteed. 
The mountainous areas make up 25 percent of Granma's provincial 
territory, of which an area of approximately 900 km has been 
electrified. 

</TEXT>

