<H3> <TI>   French Aid Ship Unable To Dock, Unload </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2803215894 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1900 
GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2803215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have learned that the Galis Bay allegedly left 
Haiti today at noon bound for the Dominican Republic. The Galis 
Bay, a French humanitarian aid ship carrying 530 tons of food, 
arrived offshore on 25 March but could not dock, sources say, 
because National Port Administration [APN] officials refused to 
grant permission. Several people, notably members of the 
Revolutionary Front for the Promotion and Progress of Haiti, 
have been demonstrating in front of APN offices since 25 March 
to protest the arrival of this ship. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

