<F P=100> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   TSE Reports La Paz Election Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2803132794 San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY in Spanish 26 Mar 
94 p 29 </F>

<F P=103> PA2803132794 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador EL DIARIO DE HOY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After long hours of waiting and lengthy discussions 
with members of the departmental electoral boards, at 
approximately 1900 last night, the Supreme Electoral Tribunal 
(TSE) reported the official results of the presidential election 
in La Paz Department. According to TSE President Luis Arturo 
Zaldivar, the results widely favored the governing Nationalist 
Republican Alliance Party, which obtained 35,081 valid votes. 
The leftist coalition of the Farabundo Marti National Liberation 
Front, Democratic Convergence, and the National Revolutionary 
Movement obtained 12,409 votes, and the Christian Democratic 
Party obtained 12,557. 
  The remaining political organizations obtained the following 
votes: Authentic Christian Movement, 462 votes; Unity Movement, 
1,505 votes; National Conciliation Party, 5,820 votes; and the 
National Solidarity Movement, 542 votes. According to the report 
provided by the departmental boards, the total number of votes 
contested was 256; 4,280 were annulled for several reasons; and 
1,903 voters abstained. 
  The TSE president said those were the first official results 
he could provide because the departmental boards discuss every 
case to reach an agreement. He said, however, he had personally 
asked the board members to speed up the counting process so as 
to give the people the final results of the presidential 
election this afternoon. He added once the vote-counting process 
ends and the TSE reports those results, the tribunal will 
immediately proceed to make the legal call for the second round 
of the presidential election, in accordance with the 
Constitution and electoral law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

