<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Between Government, Rebels `Imminent' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2903012194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2903012194 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While the signing of an overall agreement on human 
rights with immediate verification between the General Command 
of the Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity [URNG], the 
Guatemalan Government, and the Army is imminent, the two sides 
continue discussing the final text of the document, according to 
a CERIGUA dispatch. 
  Luis Becker, a member of the URGN's Political-Diplomatic 
Commission, said the document's signing will mark a new phase in 
the country's social and political life, where daily practice 
will determine whether it is possible to reduce the gap between 
the proposals on human rights and the devastating reality the 
country has faced. 
  Becker did not give any details of the agreement, but he 
described it as a positive step and a victory for the Guatemalan 
people, as well as a victory for all sectors that have struggled 
to maintain the values and principles of real democracy. 

</TEXT>

