<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Carles Wants Foreign Debt Talks Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2703020994 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2703020994 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] According to Ruben Dario Carles, presidential 
candidate for the Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement, 
National Renewal Movement, and the Civic Renewal Party, Panama 
should suspend debt negotiations with private banks. Professor 
Carles has said that although the government has stopped trying 
to reach an agreement on the foreign debt with commercial banks, 
these efforts will now limit the financial actions of the new 
government. Therefore, the next president, whoever he may be, 
and his team will have played no role in those negotiations. For 
this reason, he hopes these negotiations are suspended 
immediately. 
  [Begin recording] [Carles] Despite the goodwill and great 
effort made by the negotiatiors -- and I admit that the work 
done so far by Delia Cardenas, planning and economic policy 
minister, is very commendable -- I feel it would be advisable to 
immediately suspend those talks. 
  [Reporter] Why? 
  [Carles] The country is not in any condition to take on the 
responsibility of paying 3 billion balboas and to obtain, if 
possible, a special consideration or adjustment. I think we can 
achieve our goal of being in a better position later. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

