<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   MIR Reacts With Silence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2803212094 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2803212094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sucre -- The decision of former President Jaime 
Paz Zamora to withdraw from political activities has caused 
surprise in the city. Paz Zamora admitted making mistakes but 
not commiting crimes during his government. 
  The news hit Movement of the Revolutionary Left [MIR] 
followers the hardest. They took the news in silence. The 
possibility of a meeting of party leaders to analyze the issue 
here has not been ruled out. The population, meanwhile, 
compares Jaime Paz Zamora with a captain who abandoned ship 
without clarifying the accusations against his party. 
  Chuquisaca Peasant Leader Octavio Flores said he was 
surprised because politicians involved in trafficking are not 
tried based on Law 1008. Bolivian jails contain many peasants 
who were involved in drug production out of need and now are 
serving sentences of up to 15 years. On the other hand, the 
trafficking kingpins have laws of repentance or are able to hide 
behind political activities. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

