<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Preliminary Ruling Confirms Increase </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2903005694 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2903005694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Supreme Court [STF] has approved a 
preliminary ruling in favor of the legislative branch employees 
union by 10 votes against one. This represents the suspension 
of the government decision to withhold 10.9 percent of their 
March salaries. 
  This is really a partial preliminary ruling, because the STF 
has not decided whether the wage increase should be immediately 
paid. The STF has determined that the government should adopt 
the necessary measures to have the difference deposited in the 
Bank of Brazil in the accounts of the Chamber of Deputies, the 
Senate, and the National Accounting Office. The money will 
remain at the disposal of the STF in special interest-earning 
accounts until the STF issues a definitive ruling, something 
that will probably take place in May. 
  In order to continue with the trial, Justice Ilmar Galvao 
will ask for more information from Congress and from President 
Itamar Franco, who will have 30 days to answer the STF. Soon 
after, the attorney general must give his opinion on the case. 
  The preliminary ruling issued today only favors legislative 
branch employees. In making a final ruling the STF will take 
into account the administrative decision made on 10 March, when 
it decided that judicial branch salaries should be converted 
into the URV [real value unit] rate established on the 20th of 
each month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

